       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $8.605 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $16.845 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing
       the President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       The FY 2026 cost of the CPS Middle Tier of Acquisition effort is $798.337 million, including RDT&E and procurement of prototype units. The Department will
       certify FYDP funding in a future budget submission.

       FY 2026 adjustment of +$171.917 million mitigates funding gap to the Navy Cost Estimate, which was the result of a program re-plan incorporating additional
       activities undertaken to increase technical confidence required for Navy fielding and increased costs associated with schedule impacts; adjustment includes an
       increase of +$20.000 million for hypersonics science and technology development.

       FY2026 adjustment of -$32.881 million to account for rate/misc adjustments.

