                                                             Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals               0.000       0.000      58.000      0.000     58.000$$, $$$$, $$The Marine Corps will use a spiral approach for capability insertion into TACAIR. MUX TACAIR Increment I will rapidly accelerate the time between development and
fielding, ensuring rapid and relevant capability delivery of a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) to the warfighter. This approach will use an acquisition and contracting
path allowing multiple concurrent technology insertions (development, integration, and test) through spiral development. Each spiral will have an associated MVP that
is operationally relevant and balances schedule and technical complexity. The requirements within each MVP spiral will detail a minimum set of threshold capabilities
required for training and tactics development with a unit of employment (e.g., fleet squadron). MVP development spirals include enhancements for multiple capabilities
in the areas of: C2, EW, mission computer and datalinks. Each spiral will include SETR events aligned with an MVP configuration that supports demonstration and
evaluation. Three (3) total OTAs will award in FY 2025 for prototyping and demonstration of Increment I capabilities. These activities support an Acquisition Decision
Memorandum (ADM) for Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) Rapid Prototyping entry.

