D. Acquisition Strategy
The MUX acquisition strategy leverages organic government resources, competitive and sole-source contract awards, and rapid acquisition approaches to conduct
development, testing, experimentation, prototyping, concept refinement and risk reduction of advanced payloads, system architectures, mission control capabilities,
ground control stations, networking and communications infrastructure, and new unmanned aircraft systems. Additionally, future MUX capabilities will leverage other
services and government agencies with current technologies in development and will be available at a relatively mature technology.




