       The following iASE milestones were changed due to additional complexity of integration of the iASE Programmer with the CASS to maintain the I-Level
       maintenance capability, and additional requirements for F/A-18E/F integration of iASE Programmer including the Multi-Layered Obstructed Brokered Hub (MOB
       Hub). iASE Test and Evaluation Master Plan (TEMP) 1QFY24 to 4QFY25, PDR 1QFY24 to 3QFY24, CDR 3QFY24 to 2QFY25, SW TRR 3QFY25 to 4QFY26,
       Life Cycle Sustainment Plan (LCSP) 1QFY24 to 4QFY24, SW Development End 4QFY25 to 3QFY26, and Consolidated F/A- 18 Aircraft Weapons Integration Lab
       Start/Unit Qual to F/A- 18 Integration event starts 2QFY25. Removed M-Demo since it is part of OT.

       The following expendable countermeasure infrared countermeasure (IRCM) and RFCM effectiveness and advanced RFCM development milestones were
       changed based on aircraft and range availability and to optimize available test assets. CH-53K IRCM Modeling and Simulation (M&S) Start 1QFY26 to 1QFY25,
       MH-60 RFCM flight test 2QFY24 to 1QFY25, RR-203 award 3QFY25 to 1QFY26, Advanced Expendable Device (AED) DT flight test and AED OT flight test
       consolidate and moved to 4QFY26, RR-203 effectiveness flight test in FY2026 re-characterized to Advanced RFCM flight test and moved to 4QFY26. Re-named
       AED Qual milestone (2QFY26) to AED Qual and Safe Separation event starting 4QFY25. P-8 IRCM ground to air flight test delayed awaiting flight clearance for
       CC dispenser. P-8 countermeasure effectiveness flight test type in FY2026 will be determined based on aircraft and range availability.

       Project Unit 3327/MAGTF EW Aviation Development: Due to deficiencies in AN/ALQ-231(V)4 MV-22 testing and delays caused by aircraft availability,
       programmatic adjustments were implemented to reallocate funding to better meet the Fleet's emergent operational requirements. As a result, AN/ALQ-231(V)5
       development is delayed, quantities of AN/ALQ-231(V)4 MV-22 variant B-kits were reduced in previous fiscal years with funding realigned towards the AN/
       ALQ-231(V)3 BLK II (UH-1Y) effort to address urgent Fleet needs. The PB 2026 schedule reflects all programmatic updates accounting for the development,
       testing and production of different IT-II variants reflective of Fleet operational requirements.


       Technical:
       Project Unit 3309/Assault Survivability Optimization: Updated test asset quantities for CC, iASE and AED.




